text.section:
If the governing body of the county enacts a law reducing the assessment of personal property, personal property other than operating personal property of a public utility is subject to county property tax on:
90% of its value for the first taxable year beginning after enactment of the law;
80% of its value for the second taxable year beginning after enactment of the law;
70% of its value for the third taxable year beginning after enactment of the law;
60% of its value for the fourth taxable year beginning after enactment of the law;
50% of its value for the fifth taxable year beginning after enactment of the law;
40% of its value for the sixth taxable year beginning after enactment of the law;
30% of its value for the seventh taxable year beginning after enactment of the law;
20% of its value for the eighth taxable year beginning after enactment of the law;
10% of its value for the ninth taxable year beginning after enactment of the law; and
0% of its value for the tenth taxable year beginning after enactment of the law and for each taxable year thereafter.
